<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n29220c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n29" href="#n29220c">N29 (VI.B.21)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n29all.htm#n29220c"> 220(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Tom Gate / kopecks <font face="wake">D</font>a</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">His experiences with an exorbitant <i>drojky</i>-driver at St. Petersburg are worthy of record. They remind one of a story which he himself used to tell as having happened to a friend of his at Oxford. The latter had drawn up in a cab to <mark>Tom Gate</mark>, and offered the cabman a proper fare, which was, however, refused with scorn &hellip; &lsquo;After a hearty breakfast I left Liddon &hellip; and went off shopping, &amp;c., beginning with a call on Mr. Muir at No. 61, Galerne Ulitsa. I took a <i>drojky</i> to the house, having first bargained with the driver for thirty <mark><i>kopecks</i></mark>; he wanted forty to begin with. When we got there we had a little scene &hellip; The driver began by saying &ldquo;<i>Sorok</i>&rdquo; (forty) as I got out; this was a warning of the coming storm &hellip;&rsquo; <small> Stuart Dodgson Collingwood, <a name="SDCL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SDCL"><cite title="source">The Life and Letters of Lewis Carroll</cite></a> ([1912]) 106</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
